The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Twin treat from Torrent

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, Dec. 15: Torrent Pharmaceuticals Ltd has declared a 1:1 bonus issue and reduced the face value of its shares from Rs 10 to Rs 5 per share.

 After the stock split, the company shareholders will get two shares of the new face value for every one held.

 Moreover, the board has decided that shareholders will get a bonus issue of one share for every one held, on a post-split basis. 

 As a result, shareholders of Torrent Pharma will get four shares with a face value of Rs 5 for every existing one of Rs 10. Torrent Pharma has convened an extraordinary general meeting (EGM) on January 25 to obtain shareholders approval for these proposals.

 According to Torrent Pharma, the stock split and the bonus issue will help balance the capital structure of the company, reward shareholders and improve liquidity.

 On the Bombay Stock Exchange today, shares of Torrent Pharma opened at Rs 899.85, shot to an intra-day high of Rs 929 and closed at Rs 861.45. 




